│ stop({"edit_points": [[1380, 1380, "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the  │
│ Issue: The assertion failure occurs because there's a recipe (`VPIRInstruction`) that has an underlying          │
│ instruction with poison-generating flags (like NSW on add instructions) but doesn't inherit from                 │
│ `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`. The `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` function assumes that any recipe with poison-generating │
│ flags must be a `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`, but `VPIRInstruction` breaks this assumption.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s     │
│ Log: The log shows the assertion failing in `VPlanTransforms.cpp:1926` with the message about finding an         │
│ instruction with poison-generating flags not covered by `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`. The reproducer contains `add nsw  │
│ i64` instructions which have the NSW (No Signed Wrap) flag - a poison-generating flag.\n\n3. Root Cause          │
│ Analysis: Examining the VPlan.h file reveals that `VPIRInstruction` (line 1380) inherits directly from           │
│ `VPRecipeBase` rather than from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags`. However, `VPIRInstruction` wraps actual LLVM              │
│ `Instruction` objects that can have poison-generating flags (like NSW, NUW, fast math flags). When               │
│ `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes` processes these recipes, it fails the assertion because the recipe type doesn't    │
│ match the expected `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` for instructions with poison-generating flags.\n\n4. Proposed Edit      │
│ Point(s): Change `VPIRInstruction` to inherit from `VPRecipeWithIRFlags` instead of `VPRecipeBase`. This         │
│ requires updating line 1380 in llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h from `class VPIRInstruction : public        │
│ VPRecipeBase {` to `class VPIRInstruction : public VPRecipeWithIRFlags {`.\n\n5. Conclusion: This fix ensures    │
│ that `VPIRInstruction` properly handles poison-generating flags from its underlying instruction, making it       │
│ compatible with the assumptions in `dropPoisonGeneratingRecipes`. The change is minimal and maintains the        │
│ existing functionality while fixing the assertion failure."})                                                    │
